Dirigo Elementary School
March 27 at 2:03 PM ·

Attention DES Parents, Guardians & Friends. We are at this point closing DES until further notice (even Mr. Swan is being kicked out). This will allow our awesome custodial crew the chance to completely clean the building. As noted in the Superintendent's letter, DES will no longer be a food pick up location. The only two locations for food pick up will be the high school and the middle school. We will NOT be checking the phones here at DES, so if you have school related questions, please contact the Central Office at (207-562-4300). Stay Safe Everyone!

post_text: Good afternoon. This is an important call from RSU 56. Please listen carefully. The RSU 56 schools will be closed initially from Monday, March 16th through Friday, March 27th. This decision was made in consultation with many stakeholders and out of an abundance of caution to follow the rapidly changing guidance regarding enhancing social distancing efforts to flatten the curve of COVID-19. This decision has not been made lightly and we certainly empathize and understand the significant burden this will cause families in the coming days. We will evaluate the decision in the coming weeks and continue to update all of you regularly. There will be more information shared tomorrow afternoon including details concerning providing continuity of learning opportunities and access to food options. Additional information will be shared on our social media sites. Staff will be reporting to work tomorrow, Monday, March 16, 2020.

post_text: Today the Freshmen class at Dirigo High School was out in the community working on Community Service. Ms. Fletcher's homeroom took part in the community service day and went to the Pine Grove Cemetery in Canton to work with the "Cemetery Ladies" and other volunteers to learn about stone cleaning and to help clean some stones, and work on documenting the layout of the cemetery. During the five hours the students were there, they cleaned 39 stones and learned the proper techniques on how to clean stones and a lot about history in Canton. This group of students did an awesome job giving back to one of the four communities that make up RSU 56.

post_text:
JMG Student Officers Selected -

We would like to take a moment to recognize an amazing group of students who were elected to be JMG Officers. These students earned their positions by creating anonymous speeches and running in our election. We chose to do anonymous speeches to ensure people were voting on the merit of a candidate's ideas and leadership qualities (as outlined in their respective speeches) rather than on popularity.

These awesome young leaders will be attending JMG's Leadership Education Conference on October 17th and 18th at Pine Tree Camp in Rome, ME with many other area JMG groups.

Please congratulate them if you see them.

Jenn Decker
Arianna Boulanger
Arianna Ham
Tessa Amadei
Ian Salvati
Ashley Virgin

post_text:
DHS Football Update:

It is important to note that a false rumor has been spreading that the move to disband varsity football was somehow connected to the budget. The proposed 2019-20 budget has funds to support a varsity football program. RSU 56 has every intention of supporting a varsity program; the only reason it was disbanded this year was due to safety concerns.

RSU 56 is excited to report that it appears we will be able to field a JV football team as enough players have indicated that they will continue to play this year. RSU 56 will petition the MPA to allow us to move to a varsity 8-man team for next season.
text:
DHS Football Update:

It is important to note that a false rumor has been spreading that the move to disband varsity football was somehow connected to the budget. The proposed 2019-20 budget has funds to support a varsity football program. RSU 56 has every intention of supporting a varsity program; the only reason it was disbanded this year was due to safety concerns.

RSU 56 is excited to report that it appears we will be able to field a JV football team as enough players have indicated that they will continue to play this year. RSU 56 will petition the MPA to allow us to move to a varsity 8-man team for next season.

post_text: RSU 56 has decided to disband the varsity football team for the remainder of the 2019 season. This decision came after the athletic director, superintendent of schools and board chair heard from the football coaches that the current roster poses safety risks for our students. Dirigo High School began the football season with a limited roster and has experienced injuries that have further depleted that roster. The football coaches are confident that the current roster could safely play a JV schedule for the remainder of the school year. Superintendent Doyen noted, “Safety is our first priority.” Provided that there is sufficient student interest at Dirigo High School, Jess McGreevey, Athletic Director, will petition the MPA for a waiver so that Dirigo High School might move to an 8-man team for the 2020 football season.
